In England, in the seven days to 05 March, there were 34,330 new confirmed cases (61.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 February, there were 51,540 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 33% (17,210 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 10 March is 3,707,999 (6,587.7 cases per 100,000 population).
